<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Definition of clinical biochemistry, laboratory safety, regulation of glucose, signs of heart damage, water, sodium and potassium metabolism related diseases, hydrogen ion homeostasis and blood gases, renal physiology and function, kidney diseases, clinical enzymology, liver function and diseases, cholesterol and triglyceride metabolism , diabetes mellitus, calcium, magnesium and phosphate metabolism and diseases, changes in plasma proteins in various diseases, coronary artery disease, tumor markers, thyroid hormone biosynthesis and thyroid diseases, hormone regulation and secretion mechanisms, reference values</Data></Cell>
