<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">02.04.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1) Introduction to Clinical Pharmacy and the History of Clinical Pharmacy. Pharmaceutical Care and Application Processes
2) Patient-Oriented Concepts, Definitions, and Educational Programs: Current Status Worldwide and in Türkiye
3) Roles and Responsibilities of the Clinical Pharmacist
4) Systematic Approaches in Therapy – Case Analysis and Problem Solving
5) The Importance of Patient Education and Adherence in Clinical Pharmacy Practice: Patient Education Methods and Effective Communication Techniques
6) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Upper Respiratory Tract Infections and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment I
(Common Cold, Influenza, Vaccination, and Current Treatment Practices)
7) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Upper Respiratory Tract Infections and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment II
(Sinusitis, Pharyngitis, Otitis Media, and Treatment Options)
8) Midterm Examination Week
9) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Pain Management and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment
10) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Diarrhea and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment
11) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Constipation and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment
12) Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach to Peptic Ulcer and Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease and the Pharmacist’s Role in Treatment
13) Prescription Dispensing and Patient Counseling Practices in a Simulated Pharmacy Setting
14) Prescription Dispensing and Patient Counseling Practices in a Simulated Pharmacy Setting</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429746&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
