<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Faculty of Pharmacy (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">17</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHAR 416</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic First Aid</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">26.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic life support. What is First Aid? General Principles and Life Chain Steps, General Approach to a Case with Trauma, General Approach to a Case with Bleeding and First Aid Principles, General Approach to Fractures and Dislocations and First Aid Principles, General Approach to Spinal Trauma Case and First Aid Principles, General Approach to Head Trauma Case and First Aid Principles , General Approach to Chest Trauma Case and First Aid Principles, Syncope, Loss of Consciousness, General Approach to Stroke Case and First Aid Principles, Chest Pain - General Approach to a Patient with Heart Attack and First Aid Principles, Automatic External Defibrillator Use, General Approach to Poisoned Case Aid Principles, First Aid Guidelines for Choking and Electrocution</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429866&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Faculty of Pharmacy (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">17</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHAR 440</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Pharmaceutical Biotechnology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">23.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to biotechnology; the role of biotechnology in drug development and production, related basic concepts and applications; isolation of macromolecules; nucleic acid replication methods and their use in biotechnology; recombinant DNA technology and applications in the field of pharmaceuticals; hybridoma technology and monoclonal antibody production; antisense technology and applications; gene therapy and gene delivery systems; cell-based therapy; physicochemical properties and formulation of biopharmaceuticals; microbiological transformation techniques applied in biosynthesis of corticosteroids, plant tissue and organ culture techniques, fermentation techniques and their applications in the pharmaceutical industry; biologics, vaccines and serums</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429855&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Faculty of Pharmacy (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">17</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHAR 462</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Pharmacotherapy</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">14.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to the endocrine system and pituitary hormones, diabetes drugs, estrogens, androgens, thyroid hormone and drugs used in the treatment of thyroid diseases, adrenal hormones, drugs used in urological diseases and lifestyle drugs, drugs used in obesity and bone diseases, drugs used in dermatological diseases, drugs used in anemia, vitamins, drugs effective on the gastrointestinal system</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429768&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Faculty of Pharmacy (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">17</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHAR 472</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Clinical Pharmacy II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">13.01.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1) Medication Use During Pregnancy and the Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach
2) Medication Use During Lactation and the Clinical Pharmacist’s Approach
3) Risk Factors, Complications, Non-Pharmacological Treatment, and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist in the Management of Hypertension
4) Pharmacological Treatment of Hypertension and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
5) Pharmacological Treatment of Allergic Rhinitis and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
6) Risk Factors, Complications, Non-Pharmacological Treatment, and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist in the Management of Diabetes Mellitus
7) Pharmacological Treatment of Diabetes Mellitus and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
8) Midterm Examination
9) Risk Factors, Complications, and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist in the Management of Asthma
10) Pharmacological Treatment of Asthma, Inhalation Dosage Forms, and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
11) Pharmacological Treatment of Acne Vulgaris and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
12) Pharmacological Treatment of Anxiety Disorders and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
13) Pharmacological Treatment of Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist
14) Pharmacological Treatment of Erectile Dysfunction and the Role of the Clinical Pharmacist</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429773&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
