<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Faculty of Pharmacy (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">17</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHAR 589</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL) Training</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.01.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course provides a comprehensive overview of the function and future role of the Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL) position in the pharmaceutical industry. Throughout the training, students gain the core competencies required for the MSL role, including communication skills, field activities, medical strategy development, and therapeutic area knowledge. The course also covers clinical trial structures, advisory board management, techniques for responding to medical inquiries, and processes for creating medical–marketing materials. The impact of artificial intelligence technologies on pharmaceutical research and development as well as medical affairs is explained through detailed examples. Fundamental AI concepts, use cases in healthcare, and the digital competencies specific to MSLs are addressed. Through real case studies, participants are expected to develop the ability to conduct AI-based analyses. By the end of the course, students will have the knowledge, skills, and digital capabilities needed to work as an MSL in today’s pharmaceutical industry.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429945&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
