<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Origins: Preconditions for the “movies”
Silent Films and the Narrative in Films
Who invented movies? (Selected “players”)
Films: Thomas Edison Program: Sandow The Strong Man (1894)
Edwin S. Porter Program: Great Train Robbery (1903)
Georges Méliès, Trip to the Moon (1902)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=429810&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
